If you have an option, please do not stay at this hotel! Very bad service and smelling dirty room
review 2:
The service was terrible.
i booked a room, when i would like to check in early i ask theres a room available but they told me to check in at 2 pm, ok, i leave for an hour to brought a meal, when i am back to check in my room that i booked, they handed over to someone else. I HAVE PAID THAT ROOMS DUDE AND THERES NO APPOLOGIZE FROM THE STAFF, INSTEAD THEY BLAME ME COZ LEAVING TO BROUGHT A MEAL.. THANKS TO THAT I LOST MY MONEY FOR 200K ++ üòäüëç
kak kapan" kalo ada guest yg udah bayar kamarnya, kamarnya jangan di handed over ke orang lain..
review 3:
Worst room I have ever stayed in. I arrived and was send to my room. I had to pay right than.
I looked around in the room and felt disgusted. I have never ever had such a room. It is worse than on the photos(my camera is Not the best).
The mirror was dirty, the towel for the feet was partly Black, the nightstand was lying on the floor, the walls were dirty, but the bathroom was the worst. It was moldy everywhere, water lime and dirt in the toilet and all around the Tiles. This has not been cleaned for a while.

review 5:
Rooms can be small

Some hotels may not be as clean as others

Service may not be as consistent across all hotels

There have been some reports of fraud and scams related to OYO bookings

name: Super Capital O 2166 Elitya Stay
address: Jl. Tukad Badung XVIII B No.77, Renon, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80226, Indonesia
review 1:
Worse hotel experience in Bali!
Bed and Linen didn't look clean nor smell good.
The towels were absolutely disgusting and the staff didn't give any replacement when asked for.
Bathroom was dirty and the toilet it's itself was broken.
I definitely do t recommend!
review 2: The room is clean and decent. The staff is also friendly, but not so helpful. I was traveling with my mom abd 8-month baby bringing some luggage, but none of them helped me when I was about to check out. The breakfast was awful, you either get instant noodle, a piece of omelette, or two pieces of pancake and toast. It was also pretty far from some restaurants. There was only a fried chicken restaurant and two small shops in the neighborhood. But, if you only look for a place to stay the night for work or business, it is worth the price.
review 3:
I booked last minute and the staff said room was ready. But went to the room, there was no soap and even toilet paper
Bathroom was dirty. But the room itself was good
review 4: Stay here for 2 nights and it was amazing, and the only problem is the room is little bit smelled of cigarettes smoke. Staff was polite.
review 5: The staff doesnt even know there is a guest in the room and just when to turn off the electricity very bad attitude doesnt apologize,

name: Cove Ransha Stay
address: Jl. Tukad Badung XVIII No.mor 38, Renon, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80226, Indonesia
review 1:
I arrived at this hotel at 11pm and only upon arrival that the staff told me that they were overbooked. I asked the manager to assist me in looking for another accommodation as it was in the middle of the night and I was not familiar with the area but he told me that it was my own problem.

I told them that they could have tried calling to inform me via my local number that was in my booking and they could've called to ensure that I knew but again, he shrugged off responsibility.  As a solo traveling female, I feel that the hotel and its manager could have minimally helped me in looking for another accommodation instead of just stranding me outside their hotel.

Would never recommend this hotel. I can't imagine if I had a child or elderly with me on a family holiday.
review 2:
I don't think I can find such a clean place at this price.
The staff were so friendly and were always cleaning and working.
I think you can take a restüòÄ
If I go to Denpasar again
I'm going back here
review 3: Cove Ransha Stay Bali is a great option for budget-minded travelers looking for a comfortable and convenient place to stay near Sanur. The property is clean, well-located, and has friendly staff. I would definitely recommend it to anyone looking for a great value for money in Bali
review 4:
Super loud room near the streets with dogs barking at night. Bad odour in washroom.

Sprayed baigon or other bad smelling chemicals in the air before check in. I got allergic

I was requesting 2 times for the quiet room and when I checked in, I was given the loudest room instead.

At night lights on second floor outside are switched on. And staff don't want to turn it off, the curtains are not fully covering the window, so the room is full of light at night from the outside, this is aweful.

During the rain the rooftop leaks in the room on 2nd floor.

When the weather is windy, the doors are shaking and it is very loud.

Hot water finishes in a few minutes after starting using it.
review 5: I'm obsessed with this hotel! It's wayyy beyond my expectation, I even got a sunset view at my balcony! I booked it on agoda and i got a really good deal, when i first got there, I was amazed by the facility (free flow water, electric kettle, dental kit, Netflix!, stabil internet, room service) and hospitality! I can say it's the best budget hotel that I've ever visited! The staffs are lovely, the atmosphere is super calm and perfect, the room is super clean and comfy. I stayed for a week and I got no complaints at all (oh! I think they have a curfew at 11 pm but the staff will open the door if you call them) Please keep up the good service! Will definitely recommend this to everyone and will come back!
